principal_diagnosis: POST PARTUM HEMORRHAGE. MASSIVE BLOOD LOSS.
treatment:
SHE WAS INDUCED WENT INTO LABOUR AND DELIVERED A LIVE MALE INFANT WHO SCORED 8/1, 9/5, 10/10 WEIGHT 3005g. PLACENTA WAS COMPLETE. SHE DEVELOPED HEMORRHAGE IMMEDIATELY PLACENTA WAS EXTRACTED. UTERUS WAS WELL CONTRACTED. GIVEN SYNTOCINON IVF AND TRANEXAMIC ACID. SHE WAS ASSESSED AND FOUND TO HAVE SUSTAINED BLEEDING HIGH UP IN THE  THE LOWER UTERINE SEGMENT OF UPPER CERVIX. SHE WAS TAKEN TO THEATRE FOR EUA. FOUND TO BE BLEEDING FORM HIGH IN THE CERVIX WITH BLEEDERS NOT EASILY IDENTIFIABLE. DECISION TO LIGATE PARACERVICAL VESSELS MADE BUT THE BLEEDING DIDNT STOP. A DECISION TO OPEN THE ABDOMEN MADE AND IT WAS QUICKLY CONVERTED AND OPENED. FOUND WELL CONTRACTED UTERUS. OPENED INSIDE AND NOTED MULTIPLR AREAS OF OOZING. UTERINE VESSELS AND OVARIAN VESSELS LIGATED. AND SQUARE AND FIGURE 8 SUTURES MADE IN THE UTERUS CAVITY. UTERSU AND ABDOMEN WAS CLOSED AFTER CONFIRMING REDUCED BLEEDING.  PATIENT REVERSED AND TAKEN TO PACU. AT PACU NOTED THE VITALS WORSENING AND ON EXAM NOTED TO STILL BE BLEEDING AND WAS TAKEN IN FOR REOPENING AND TOTAL HYSTERECTOMY PERFORMED. 
ON DAY 2 NOTED TO BE HAVING DISCOMFORT ON THE LEFT ILIAC AND LUMBAR AREA. A MASS WAS FELT AND ULTRASOUND REVEALED RETROPERITONEAL HEMATOMA OF ABOUT 400 MLS. LAPAROTOMY PERFORMED AND HEMATOMA EVACUATED. SHE HAS DONE WELL. VITAL STABLE. PAIN WELL CONTROLLED. BREAST ARE ACTIVE.

AN ULTRASOUND DONE SHOWED VERY THIN LOWER SEGMENT. SHE WAS A PARA 1+2 G4 AND  ANC PROFILE WAS NOT AVAILABLE. SHE HAD RECEIVED DEXAMETHASONE  A WEEK PRIOR IN PREPARATION FOR EARLY DELIVERY. SHE HAS DONE WELL WITH MINIMAL INCISIONAL PAIN, ACTIVE BREASTS AND BABY BREAST FEEDING WEL. LOCHIA MINIMAL. HOWEVER  HAS HAD FRONTAL HEADACHE AND NECK PAINS. WHICH SHOULD SUBSIDE ON ANALGESIA.
